                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've had great experiences with GMs so far in WoW, but I also had a really good experience with GM staff in EQ. I think part of the reason is that I keep out of trouble and so don't need GMs to police the population and the few errors I've had to deal with including trade bugs in EQ or instances not being reset in WoW have been dealt with in a very timely fashion and always with the utmost courtesy and professionalism. Perhaps I'm simply lucky but when I only need to call upon customer service 3 or 4 times during the lifetime of a game and all those issues are resolved extremely well I have trouble critisizing their service.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />When a government has ceased to protect the lives, liberty and property of the people, from whom its legitimate powers are derived, and for the advancement of whose happiness it was instituted, and so far from being a guarantee for the enjoyment of those inestimable and inalienable rights, becomes an instrument in the hands of evil rulers for their oppression. - Declaration of Independence of the State of Texas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
